<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>27<percent/> of 108</li> 
<li>3<percent/> of 2375</li> 
<li>85<percent/> of 76</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>B: 3<percent/> of 2375</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{85}\%\cdot{76}={64.6}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{27}\%\cdot{108}={29.16}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{3}\%\cdot{2375}={71.25}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 3<percent/> of 2375 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

